  <title translate="true">Number and Operator Buttons</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Numb</text><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">er and Operator Buttons</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The number and operator buttons in the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Formula_Editor" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Formula Editor</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> all work the same way: when the user clicks one of the buttons, the text displayed on the button will be inserted in the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Formula_Text_Box" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Formula text box</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> at the position of the cursor. If any text in the formula is selected, it will be replaced. See </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Operators" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Operators</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> for more information on the meanings of the operators.</text></para>
  </body>
